<p>Extreme. Intense. A variety of shapes and sizes. From the amateur to the professional, Ping Pong, Table Tennis, Wiff Waff- whatever you wish to call it - we have it all. </p><p>We'll be having weekly social and training sessions as well as running 2 teams in the Premier League this year, with the possibility of a 3rd team in Div 1 should the interest be sufficient.</p><p>We are hoping to build on the success of last year in which we won both the Premiership and Div 1 Titles. If you have any questions please do not hesitate to get in touch with myself, Rob or Alice. </p><p>JBCTTC Facebook page: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/#!/groups/207021719451176/">https://www.facebook.com/#!/groups/207021719451176/</a></p><p>Presiedent: Matt Rowland - <a href="mailto:m.r.rowland@durham.ac.uk">m.r.rowland@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>A Captain: Rob Young - <a href="mailto:robert.young@durham.ac.uk">robert.young@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p>B Captain: Alice Driscoll - <a href="mailto:a.e.driscoll@durham.ac.uk">a.e.driscoll@durham.ac.uk</a> </p><p><img src="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/050.jpg" width="474" height="354"></p><p>Current JCR President Will Kendall (right) seeing off a hopeless Matt Gillet with his favourite lime green bat. </p><p>&nbsp;</p>